WEBVTT

00:00:01.320 --> 00:00:03.090
Babies start learning from birth.

00:00:04.710 --> 00:00:08.370
They learned through the experiences and
interactions they have with the people in

00:00:08.370 --> 00:00:09.150
their lives

00:00:09.390 --> 00:00:10.920
as well as their surroundings.

00:00:12.660 --> 00:00:13.660
For example.

00:00:13.770 --> 00:00:15.840
When you respond
to your baby's cry.

00:00:16.290 --> 00:00:17.850
Your baby learns that you love her.

00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:19.480
And care for her.

00:00:20.640 --> 00:00:22.830
And when you cuddle
smile at your baby.

00:00:23.190 --> 00:00:25.410
It releases chemicals
in your baby's body

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:27.030
which makes him feel good

00:00:27.330 --> 00:00:28.680
and helps him bond with you.

00:00:29.790 --> 00:00:33.090
The experiences and interactions
you share with your baby

00:00:33.245 --> 00:00:35.640
form millions of
connections in her brain

00:00:35.940 --> 00:00:40.530
your relationship with your baby helps
her develop the skills she needs for life.

00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:45.810
Settling and comforting your
baby helps him trust and rely on you

00:00:46.140 --> 00:00:49.170
and gives him confidence to
form relationships with other people.

00:00:50.010 --> 00:00:53.970
Noticing and responding to your
baby's needs helps calm and settle her.

00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:57.000
So she can do other
things like play or sleep.

00:00:58.290 --> 00:01:01.410
Even if you don't know why
your baby is unsettled will crying.

00:01:01.830 --> 00:01:03.360
It's important to comfort her.

00:01:03.930 --> 00:01:04.930
Picking her up

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:05.910
cuddling her

00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:08.040
and talking to her
in a gentle voice

00:01:08.190 --> 00:01:10.110
makes her feel secure and loved.

00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:15.780
Play is a great way to interact with
your baby and help her to learn and feel loved.

00:01:16.530 --> 00:01:17.550
And at this age

00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:20.250
the best toy for
your baby is you.

00:01:21.090 --> 00:01:24.060
Games like peek-a-boo
stimulate your baby's brain

00:01:24.330 --> 00:01:27.030
and help him develop
important skills like thinking.

00:01:27.540 --> 00:01:28.540
Communicating.

00:01:28.860 --> 00:01:29.860
Socializing

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:31.000
and moving.

00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:34.170
You can play with your baby
anywhere and everywhere.

00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:36.720
Everything is new to your baby.

00:01:40.380 --> 00:01:43.830
Singing telling stories
doing tummy time.

00:01:44.310 --> 00:01:48.390
Talking or making funny sounds a
great place to play with your baby.

00:01:48.990 --> 00:01:52.770
Your baby loves hearing your voice go
up and down and watching your facial

00:01:52.770 --> 00:01:54.330
expressions as you talk to him.

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:58.121
And even though he can't talk yet
he is an excellent communicator.

00:01:59.310 --> 00:02:01.530
Talking, listening, and
responding to him

00:02:01.830 --> 00:02:04.200
builds his language and
communication skills.

00:02:05.130 --> 00:02:07.200
Your baby is an amazing learner.

00:02:07.740 --> 00:02:11.640
She's learning new things all the time
through the everyday things you do together.

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:14.160
By playing with her
and comforting her

00:02:14.310 --> 00:02:16.890
you're giving your
baby a great start in life.